1
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:29,666
[JOHN]
My daughter.

2
00:00:29,750 --> 00:00:30,958
Father.

3
00:00:32,791 --> 00:00:34,916
[JOHN] This is our chance
to turn Burgundy

4
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:37,541
into the most
powerful empire on Earth.

5
00:00:39,583 --> 00:00:42,291
[VOICES overlapping]

6
00:00:45,708 --> 00:00:46,875
[PHILIP]
Montmorency.

7
00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:20,875
♪

8
00:02:20,958 --> 00:02:23,375
[indistinct voices chattering]

9
00:02:23,458 --> 00:02:26,875
[MAN] I hereby declare,
justice has been served.

10
00:02:26,958 --> 00:02:29,083
She made a false claim
of sainthood

11
00:02:29,166 --> 00:02:30,916
and lied about her purity,

12
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:32,500
but it's over.

13
00:02:32,583 --> 00:02:34,916
She who would have plunged
France into eternal darkness

14
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,583
has perished at last.

15
00:02:37,625 --> 00:02:38,958
[MONTMORENCY gasps]

16
00:02:41,333 --> 00:02:43,958
[MONTMORENCY screaming]

17
00:02:45,916 --> 00:02:48,333
♪

18
00:03:07,041 --> 00:03:08,333
[JEANNE]
Montmorency.

19
00:03:09,583 --> 00:03:11,333
[snickers menacingly]

20
00:03:11,416 --> 00:03:12,916
[JEANNE cries softly]

21
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,791
Jeanne, what's become
of Montmorency?

22
00:03:14,875 --> 00:03:16,708
What's going on?

23
00:03:16,791 --> 00:03:17,625
You okay?

24
00:03:17,708 --> 00:03:19,416
[gasps]
What now?

25
00:03:22,541 --> 00:03:24,041
[grunting]

26
00:03:28,791 --> 00:03:31,666
No. Could this really be
happening so soon?

27
00:03:36,916 --> 00:03:38,625
[screaming]

28
00:03:38,708 --> 00:03:40,208
Jeanne, no!

29
00:03:40,291 --> 00:03:43,000
[screaming]

30
00:03:43,083 --> 00:03:44,291
I've lost him.

31
00:03:44,375 --> 00:03:46,583
I can't hear Montmorency's voice
anymore.

32
00:03:46,666 --> 00:03:48,416
It feels as though
he's truly gone.

33
00:03:49,916 --> 00:03:51,833
Montmorency!

34
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,625
Mur d'Air, was it?

35
00:03:54,708 --> 00:03:56,416
Look familiar?

36
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:57,458
[JEANNE gasps]

37
00:03:57,541 --> 00:03:59,250
[evil laughter]

38
00:04:01,208 --> 00:04:02,875
Montmorency.

39
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:05,750
[ENLIL] No, love.
You shall address me as Enlil.

40
00:04:05,833 --> 00:04:08,041
Ruler of the true Utopia,

41
00:04:08,125 --> 00:04:11,916
and king amongst
all the 72 gods.

42
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:13,416
Show some respect.

43
00:04:18,500 --> 00:04:19,958
[gasps]

44
00:04:20,041 --> 00:04:21,625
[PHILIP]
Montmorency.

45
00:04:21,708 --> 00:04:23,958
You're truly gone.

46
00:04:24,041 --> 00:04:26,291
[JOHN]
You must avenge him, daughter.

47
00:04:26,375 --> 00:04:28,166
[PHILIP gasps]
Avenge him?

48
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:29,750
[JOHN]
Yes.

49
00:04:29,833 --> 00:04:34,041
Kill the God and gain
a reputation as the God killer.

50
00:04:34,125 --> 00:04:36,208
Become the savior in black.

51
00:04:36,291 --> 00:04:37,833
Saint Philip.

52
00:04:37,916 --> 00:04:40,750
You will be known
throughout France and England.

53
00:04:40,833 --> 00:04:42,958
This shall be the foundation
for the rise

54
00:04:43,041 --> 00:04:44,666
of the Burgundian Empire.

55
00:04:44,750 --> 00:04:46,125
[PHILIP gasps]

56
00:04:46,208 --> 00:04:49,375
[JOHN] For you, my daughter,
have the upper hand.

57
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:52,666
[gasps]

58
00:04:59,958 --> 00:05:01,708
Huh?

59
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:04,291
[GLASDALE] I pulled you out
of the river, along with this.

60
00:05:06,333 --> 00:05:08,041
[PHILIP]
The Grail.

61
00:05:08,125 --> 00:05:09,250
Indeed.

62
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:25,541
The truth is,

63
00:05:25,625 --> 00:05:27,916
if that young alchemist
turned into Ulysses,

64
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,833
then my arrow
should be effective.

65
00:05:29,916 --> 00:05:31,125
That's good news.

66
00:05:31,208 --> 00:05:33,125
But unfortunately,

67
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:36,708
he also has the ability to block
my attack with a wall of air.

68
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:38,500
[PHILIP]
We can use Jeanne as a sacrifice

69
00:05:38,583 --> 00:05:40,791
and create an opening
for you to take the shot.

70
00:05:40,875 --> 00:05:42,166
[GLASDALE]
Oh?

71
00:05:42,250 --> 00:05:43,875
[PHILIP] This will be
quite a boon for you,

72
00:05:43,958 --> 00:05:46,333
as well as Lord Bedford.

73
00:05:46,416 --> 00:05:48,125
May I count on your assistance?

74
00:05:49,250 --> 00:05:51,250
-Can you do it?
-Huh?

75
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:55,583
[GLASDALE] Noire, or rather,
Princess Philip of Burgundy.

76
00:05:55,666 --> 00:05:59,250
I hear you refuse to squash
even a single insect.

77
00:05:59,333 --> 00:06:01,750
Your nickname is
Philip the Good, after all.

78
00:06:01,833 --> 00:06:02,916
[PHILIP]
Mm-hmm.

79
00:06:03,916 --> 00:06:05,291
Will you prevail?

80
00:06:07,708 --> 00:06:10,791
[PHILIP] I suppose
this must be my destiny.

81
00:06:10,875 --> 00:06:13,916
I'm fated to avenge Montmorency.

82
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,041
Now I understand this must be

83
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:18,291
why the helm
came into my possession.

84
00:06:18,375 --> 00:06:19,833
In which case,

85
00:06:19,916 --> 00:06:23,125
I shall defy my nickname,
and clothe myself in black.

86
00:06:25,208 --> 00:06:27,375
♪

87
00:06:33,375 --> 00:06:36,083
Now, should I
put my faith in you?

88
00:06:36,166 --> 00:06:37,583
[GLASDALE]
Absolutely.

89
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:40,583
[gasps]

90
00:06:40,666 --> 00:06:41,708
Oh, no.

91
00:06:43,291 --> 00:06:45,000
Pierce them both at once.

92
00:06:46,791 --> 00:06:49,208
-Die, you scum!
-[gunfire]

93
00:06:49,291 --> 00:06:50,291
Protect yourself!

94
00:06:50,375 --> 00:06:51,791
[LA HIRE groaning]

95
00:06:54,791 --> 00:06:57,125
♪

96
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:01,625
-Jeanne.
-[JEANNE] What is it?

97
00:07:01,708 --> 00:07:04,208
How long can we fight
as Ulysses?

98
00:07:04,291 --> 00:07:05,791
Not for long, I'm afraid.

99
00:07:07,291 --> 00:07:08,291
[BOTH gasp]

100
00:07:08,375 --> 00:07:09,333
[grunts]

101
00:07:09,416 --> 00:07:10,833
I'll act as your shield.

102
00:07:10,916 --> 00:07:12,666
You have to destroy
Montmorency's head.

103
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:14,416
[JEANNE gasps]

104
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:16,625
Your hearts are linked, so you
should know better than anyone.

105
00:07:16,708 --> 00:07:19,625
That creature over there
is no longer Montmorency.

106
00:07:22,291 --> 00:07:24,416
[JEANNE sobbing quietly]

107
00:07:26,041 --> 00:07:27,666
There's no time
to wrestle with it!

108
00:07:29,166 --> 00:07:31,583
[evil laughter]

109
00:07:31,666 --> 00:07:33,333
[LA HIRE]
Strike, magical bullet!

110
00:07:37,291 --> 00:07:38,583
[groans sharply]

111
00:07:40,125 --> 00:07:41,541
[LA HIRE]
Do it now.

112
00:07:41,625 --> 00:07:42,666
Go!

113
00:07:44,541 --> 00:07:46,458
♪

114
00:07:49,791 --> 00:07:51,666
[yells]

115
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:52,791
[groans]

116
00:07:54,041 --> 00:07:55,958
Could this really be the end?

117
00:08:00,208 --> 00:08:01,458
[coughs]

118
00:08:05,625 --> 00:08:06,791
[scoffs]

119
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:12,625
[ENLIL]
And now, come, my followers!

120
00:08:21,916 --> 00:08:24,958
The time of judgment
is at last upon us.

121
00:08:25,041 --> 00:08:27,375
♪

122
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:34,041
Hmm.

123
00:08:34,125 --> 00:08:35,250
It seems you have remained

124
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:37,541
in the Void Dimension
far too long.

125
00:08:38,541 --> 00:08:41,125
Hold on. This is not at all
what we expected.

126
00:08:41,208 --> 00:08:43,458
Is that monstrosity
even a Ulysses?

127
00:08:43,541 --> 00:08:46,000
I'm having doubts that my arrow
will serve its purpose.

128
00:08:46,083 --> 00:08:48,708
[ULYSSES NOIRE] This "god" made
no attempt to kill Montmorency

129
00:08:48,791 --> 00:08:50,250
and take out
the Philosopher's Stone

130
00:08:50,333 --> 00:08:51,375
from his body.

131
00:08:51,458 --> 00:08:52,958
Why do you suppose
that might be?

132
00:08:53,041 --> 00:08:54,541
Just as I suspected,

133
00:08:54,625 --> 00:08:56,708
a superior host
will be necessary.

134
00:08:56,791 --> 00:08:58,791
It's the only way
we can maintain our form

135
00:08:58,875 --> 00:09:00,583
and consciousness
at their full power.

136
00:09:00,666 --> 00:09:02,833
Oh, well, then I shall become

137
00:09:02,916 --> 00:09:05,583
the one and only god
to ever obtain a host

138
00:09:05,666 --> 00:09:06,708
for such a purpose.

139
00:09:06,791 --> 00:09:08,583
That is a Ulysses.

140
00:09:08,666 --> 00:09:10,208
Ready your bow, Glasdale.

141
00:09:13,125 --> 00:09:14,291
[XAINTRAILLES]
Damn it!

142
00:09:14,375 --> 00:09:16,666
I promised myself
I wouldn't die a virgin!

143
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:17,833
[BATARD]
What?

144
00:09:17,916 --> 00:09:19,500
I had my heart
set on you, Etienne,

145
00:09:19,583 --> 00:09:21,416
but it doesn't look like there's
any hope of that happening.

146
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:24,125
I suppose I'll just have to
settle for you, then, Batard.

147
00:09:24,208 --> 00:09:26,083
[ALL screaming]

148
00:09:28,041 --> 00:09:30,375
[ENLIL]
Utopia will be restored.

149
00:09:30,458 --> 00:09:32,375
I'll return the Earth
to its rightful state

150
00:09:32,458 --> 00:09:35,250
and there will no longer be
a place for humanity in it.

151
00:09:35,333 --> 00:09:37,958
The next generation of slaves
shall not be made in our image

152
00:09:38,041 --> 00:09:39,916
as they have been in the past.

153
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,375
They will obey our commands
without resistance

154
00:09:42,458 --> 00:09:43,916
or conscious thought.

155
00:09:45,083 --> 00:09:46,458
[NICOLAS]
Such tragedy.

156
00:09:46,541 --> 00:09:49,000
Will this be the end
of the human race?

157
00:09:49,083 --> 00:09:51,083
Is this how our species
will fall?

158
00:09:52,291 --> 00:09:53,541
What are you doing?

159
00:09:55,416 --> 00:09:58,166
I am the one who turned
the humans against their gods.

160
00:09:58,250 --> 00:10:00,541
If you need a scapegoat,
punish me.

161
00:10:00,625 --> 00:10:02,375
Burn me forever.

162
00:10:02,458 --> 00:10:04,416
Rip me apart all you want.

163
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:05,416
I don't care.

164
00:10:05,500 --> 00:10:07,458
But please spare the humans.

165
00:10:07,541 --> 00:10:08,791
Just punish me!

166
00:10:08,875 --> 00:10:10,000
Do not-- [groans]

167
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:13,208
[gasps]

168
00:10:15,416 --> 00:10:16,291
[screams]

169
00:10:16,375 --> 00:10:17,583
I'll hear no more from you.

170
00:10:17,666 --> 00:10:19,083
Just lie there helplessly

171
00:10:19,166 --> 00:10:21,708
and witness the destruction
of this false Utopia.

172
00:10:23,583 --> 00:10:26,541
[GLASDALE]
It isn't time, not yet.

173
00:10:26,625 --> 00:10:29,375
Now, respond to the sound
of my voice,

174
00:10:29,458 --> 00:10:31,083
vessel in the sky.

175
00:10:36,375 --> 00:10:38,083
♪

176
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:40,333
[gasps weakly]

177
00:10:43,250 --> 00:10:44,541
-[ULYSSES NOIRE grunts]
-[ENLIL groans]

178
00:10:44,625 --> 00:10:47,166
[ULYSSES NOIRE]
Glasdale, do it now!

179
00:10:47,250 --> 00:10:49,000
[arrow firing]

180
00:10:51,125 --> 00:10:53,791
[ULYSSES NOIRE] I dedicate
this act of revenge to you.

181
00:10:55,166 --> 00:10:57,500
I love you, Montmorency.

182
00:10:57,583 --> 00:10:58,958
I always have.

183
00:11:00,541 --> 00:11:02,541
♪

184
00:11:03,875 --> 00:11:05,708
How is that even possible?

185
00:11:05,791 --> 00:11:09,166
This story isn't over,
not just yet.

186
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:11,666
Montmorency hasn't left
this realm completely.

187
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:13,583
I can sense
his presence even now,

188
00:11:13,666 --> 00:11:15,083
waiting to be restored.

189
00:11:15,166 --> 00:11:16,958
[ULYSSES NOIRE gasps]

190
00:11:17,041 --> 00:11:20,375
[ENLIL] How long do you intend
to cling to me like this?

191
00:11:20,458 --> 00:11:21,833
-Release me!
-[groans]

192
00:11:23,916 --> 00:11:25,083
[ULYSSES NOIRE groans]

193
00:11:27,541 --> 00:11:28,958
Damn it all.

194
00:11:29,041 --> 00:11:30,833
Pathetic human.

195
00:11:34,583 --> 00:11:36,583
-[groans]
-[ENLIL] Hmm?

196
00:11:38,416 --> 00:11:40,666
[ULYSSES NOIRE groaning]

197
00:11:42,083 --> 00:11:44,250
[ULYSSES NOIRE] I couldn't tell
he was still here.

198
00:11:46,083 --> 00:11:47,458
But you could.

199
00:11:47,541 --> 00:11:49,833
You were able to feel
his presence,

200
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:51,125
and that means...

201
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:55,958
you are the only hope we have
of saving Montmorency.

202
00:11:57,833 --> 00:11:59,500
[JEANNE sighs]

203
00:11:59,583 --> 00:12:01,916
[ENLIL] Enough of this
ridiculous babbling.

204
00:12:03,625 --> 00:12:04,833
[groans]

205
00:12:06,625 --> 00:12:07,458
[chuckles]

206
00:12:09,125 --> 00:12:10,625
Montmorency!

207
00:12:10,708 --> 00:12:13,875
♪

208
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:25,208
Huh?

209
00:12:26,375 --> 00:12:27,916
Where am I?

210
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:31,791
Hello?

211
00:12:31,875 --> 00:12:33,833
Excuse me, sir.

212
00:12:33,916 --> 00:12:35,916
Have you seen my friend,
Montmorency?

213
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:37,000
Huh?

214
00:12:37,083 --> 00:12:39,458
[JEANNE]
Sorry. I, um...

215
00:12:39,541 --> 00:12:41,666
I think I've heard
Jean the Redbeard's grandson

216
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:42,791
called that before.

217
00:12:42,875 --> 00:12:44,083
There.

218
00:12:44,166 --> 00:12:45,208
The school.

219
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,000
[birds chirping]

220
00:13:00,875 --> 00:13:03,208
[MONTMORENCY] Transmutation
with the Philosopher's Stone.

221
00:13:03,291 --> 00:13:05,250
It's the ultimate secret
divine art.

222
00:13:05,333 --> 00:13:08,291
They say the Stone has the power
to grant its owner immortality.

223
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:10,083
Which means,
if we can master alchemy...

224
00:13:10,166 --> 00:13:11,000
[gasps]

225
00:13:17,250 --> 00:13:19,125
As I was saying,
if we master alchemy,

226
00:13:19,208 --> 00:13:21,416
we can make sure
no one dies in battle again.

227
00:13:23,375 --> 00:13:24,541
Was that a reaction?

228
00:13:24,625 --> 00:13:27,458
I've heard this a hundred times.

229
00:13:27,541 --> 00:13:28,500
[MONTMORENCY sighs]

230
00:13:30,291 --> 00:13:31,833
So, you're gonna buy up

231
00:13:31,916 --> 00:13:33,666
all the grimoires
you can find, then what?

232
00:13:33,750 --> 00:13:34,750
I don't know yet.

233
00:13:34,833 --> 00:13:35,958
I've read tons of them,

234
00:13:36,041 --> 00:13:37,541
and it's like
they're written in code.

235
00:13:37,625 --> 00:13:39,916
I won't get anywhere unless
that old man can teach me.

236
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:41,083
[JEANNE]
Montmorency!

237
00:13:42,125 --> 00:13:43,500
I'm so relieved.

238
00:13:43,583 --> 00:13:45,416
I was afraid
I wouldn't find you!

239
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:46,750
[chuckles]

240
00:13:49,083 --> 00:13:50,291
And who are you?

241
00:13:50,375 --> 00:13:52,250
[JEANNE] What do you mean?
It's me. Jeanne.

242
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:54,666
Only students are allowed to be
on the premises,

243
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,000
so you had better go.

244
00:13:56,083 --> 00:13:57,625
You don't wanna get in trouble.

245
00:13:57,708 --> 00:14:00,333
[JEANNE] Come on, stop playing
dumb with me, Montmorency.

246
00:14:00,416 --> 00:14:02,375
[MONTMORENCY]
Let go of me.

247
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:04,041
I do not know you.

248
00:14:04,125 --> 00:14:05,666
So, I'll thank you
not to touch me.

249
00:14:05,750 --> 00:14:06,666
Please leave.

250
00:14:10,041 --> 00:14:13,250
♪

251
00:14:13,333 --> 00:14:14,500
[gasps]

252
00:14:21,083 --> 00:14:22,375
Could it be?

253
00:14:22,458 --> 00:14:24,000
Montmorency is stuck
in his past,

254
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:25,958
reliving all his old memories?

255
00:14:26,958 --> 00:14:29,041
[PHILIP] Hey,
we should swear an oath.

256
00:14:29,125 --> 00:14:30,125
[MONTMORENCY]
Huh?

257
00:14:30,208 --> 00:14:32,000
A promise to stay
friends forever.

258
00:14:33,291 --> 00:14:34,208
Hmph.

259
00:14:34,291 --> 00:14:35,666
Well, what are we waiting for?

260
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:36,666
We solemnly swear...

261
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:38,000
That no matter what...

262
00:14:38,083 --> 00:14:40,375
Even after we graduate
from the academy...

263
00:14:40,458 --> 00:14:42,833
[ALL] We'll remain
best friends forever!

264
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:45,833
[JEANNE]
Montmorency.

265
00:14:45,916 --> 00:14:46,875
[MONTMORENCY]
You again?

266
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:51,875
Please just hear me out,
Montmorency.

267
00:14:51,958 --> 00:14:53,833
[MONTMORENCY]
How dare you?

268
00:14:53,916 --> 00:14:55,541
Don't speak to me
as though you know me.

269
00:14:55,625 --> 00:14:57,000
You must think I'm someone else.

270
00:14:57,083 --> 00:14:58,708
[JEANNE]
The Philosopher's Stone.

271
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:02,250
You split it in two
and gave me half.

272
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:05,750
I was on the verge of death
and you did it to save my life.

273
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:07,875
So many things have happened
since then.

274
00:15:07,958 --> 00:15:11,416
We went to the palace in Chinon,
and Charlotte made me a knight.

275
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:14,791
We fought together against
the English army at Orleans.

276
00:15:14,875 --> 00:15:17,291
When my heart was pierced,
you stepped in and saved--

277
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:18,750
[MONTMORENCY]
Please stop.

278
00:15:18,833 --> 00:15:21,583
You swore you'd protect me
for as long as we lived.

279
00:15:21,666 --> 00:15:22,625
No matter what!

280
00:15:22,708 --> 00:15:24,541
And you said you'd never marry.

281
00:15:24,625 --> 00:15:26,083
Like the knights
who professed allegiance

282
00:15:26,166 --> 00:15:27,291
to noblewomen,

283
00:15:27,375 --> 00:15:28,541
-maintaining their purity...
-Stop it.

284
00:15:28,625 --> 00:15:29,791
-...and devoting themselves...
-Quiet!

285
00:15:29,875 --> 00:15:30,708
...to service.

286
00:15:30,791 --> 00:15:34,208
I can't take any more!

287
00:15:35,208 --> 00:15:37,083
[JEANNE screaming]

288
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:43,875
[JEANNE]
Where am I now?

289
00:15:43,958 --> 00:15:47,041
♪

290
00:15:48,583 --> 00:15:50,041
[CATHERINE]
What are these?

291
00:15:50,125 --> 00:15:52,750
[MONTMORENCY]
My sisters are sleeping here.

292
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:54,916
The girls who were taken
to the castle.

293
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,458
I never saw them after that

294
00:15:56,541 --> 00:15:58,291
because they all died
in the tower.

295
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:01,791
They wanted to go home
and see their families again

296
00:16:01,875 --> 00:16:03,541
but when they realized
that would never happen,

297
00:16:03,625 --> 00:16:06,083
they lost all hope
and died of broken hearts.

298
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:08,666
I wish I could have saved them,
but I failed as a brother.

299
00:16:08,750 --> 00:16:11,291
No, Montmorency,
it isn't your fault.

300
00:16:11,375 --> 00:16:12,708
Jean the Redbeard did this.

301
00:16:12,791 --> 00:16:15,208
The old man has gone mad, true.

302
00:16:15,291 --> 00:16:17,666
But he became that way
only because of the war.

303
00:16:19,333 --> 00:16:21,958
The strong are the ones
who survive.

304
00:16:22,041 --> 00:16:23,958
You have to step on others,

305
00:16:24,041 --> 00:16:26,833
or else you'll get trampled
like all the rest.

306
00:16:26,916 --> 00:16:30,125
In a world that cruel,
people have no other choice

307
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:31,958
but to be like him.

308
00:16:32,041 --> 00:16:35,291
Even if we killed him,
that truth would not be changed.

309
00:16:35,375 --> 00:16:37,041
It's just how things are.

310
00:16:37,125 --> 00:16:40,791
Unless someone can end this war,
the tragedies will never cease.

311
00:16:44,708 --> 00:16:46,208
Alchemy.

312
00:16:46,291 --> 00:16:47,541
If I master this art,

313
00:16:47,625 --> 00:16:50,000
I will make sure
no one dies in battle again.

314
00:16:50,083 --> 00:16:51,666
No.

315
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:54,500
I will aim higher
and put a stop to war itself.

316
00:16:56,166 --> 00:16:57,458
[JEANNE]
Montmorency.

317
00:16:59,125 --> 00:17:01,500
-[MONTMORENCY] Hmm?
-[JEANNE] Let's go home.

318
00:17:01,583 --> 00:17:03,833
Let's work hand in hand
to end the heartbreak.

319
00:17:03,916 --> 00:17:06,083
I'm sure the two of us
can do it.

320
00:17:06,166 --> 00:17:09,750
If we work as one,
nothing can stop us.

321
00:17:09,833 --> 00:17:11,875
We cannot be together.

322
00:17:11,958 --> 00:17:13,166
[gasps]

323
00:17:14,708 --> 00:17:17,500
♪

324
00:17:23,625 --> 00:17:24,833
[JEANNE gasps]

325
00:17:33,708 --> 00:17:35,250
[JEANNE]
Is this my ribbon?

326
00:17:38,708 --> 00:17:40,291
[MONTMORENCY]
I've seen the future.

327
00:17:40,375 --> 00:17:42,833
I know what will happen to you.

328
00:17:42,916 --> 00:17:43,958
[JEANNE]
What do you mean?

329
00:17:44,041 --> 00:17:45,250
Is it bad?

330
00:17:49,250 --> 00:17:51,458
Oh, no. But this can't be.

331
00:17:51,541 --> 00:17:53,125
[MONTMORENCY]
I witnessed the flow of time,

332
00:17:53,208 --> 00:17:54,708
when I merged with Enlil.

333
00:17:55,791 --> 00:17:58,083
I learned about events
that happened in the past,

334
00:17:58,166 --> 00:17:59,875
and some that are yet to come.

335
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:02,666
Can't you feel it?

336
00:18:02,750 --> 00:18:05,041
This isn't an illusion, Jeanne.

337
00:18:05,125 --> 00:18:07,250
It's what's destined
to become of you.

338
00:18:09,500 --> 00:18:10,750
But it'll be all right,

339
00:18:10,833 --> 00:18:12,708
as long as we stay
right where we are.

340
00:18:13,916 --> 00:18:16,083
♪

341
00:18:19,541 --> 00:18:21,333
[JEANNE]
I remember this place.

342
00:18:21,416 --> 00:18:24,375
[MONTMORENCY] Yeah, it hasn't
been so long since we were here,

343
00:18:24,458 --> 00:18:26,833
and yet that day
still feels like ages ago.

344
00:18:28,791 --> 00:18:32,375
This realm isn't real,
at least not in a literal way.

345
00:18:32,458 --> 00:18:34,333
We stand outside of time.

346
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:36,916
We could settle down

347
00:18:37,000 --> 00:18:39,375
and forget all about the world
we came from.

348
00:18:41,875 --> 00:18:43,833
As long as I have you,

349
00:18:43,916 --> 00:18:45,375
I will want for nothing.

350
00:18:45,458 --> 00:18:47,875
♪

351
00:18:54,791 --> 00:18:57,041
[JEANNE]
We can't stay, Montmorency.

352
00:18:58,750 --> 00:19:01,541
I know our world
is full of sadness.

353
00:19:01,625 --> 00:19:05,458
There is war, misunderstanding,
betrayal, too.

354
00:19:05,541 --> 00:19:08,416
But I still love it,
in spite of its faults.

355
00:19:08,500 --> 00:19:09,791
Princess Charlotte's there,

356
00:19:09,875 --> 00:19:12,666
La Hire, Astaroth,
and Richemont, too.

357
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:16,208
And there's Alencon, Batard,
and even Xaintrailles.

358
00:19:16,291 --> 00:19:18,416
The Maiden Volunteer Corps,
and the villagers,

359
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:20,125
and the fairies, and...

360
00:19:20,208 --> 00:19:22,708
I cherish that world
because they're in it.

361
00:19:22,791 --> 00:19:24,625
I know you feel the same way.

362
00:19:24,708 --> 00:19:26,833
That's the whole reason
you studied alchemy.

363
00:19:26,916 --> 00:19:28,541
To make the world
a better place.

364
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:31,791
I refuse to live in a world
without you in it,

365
00:19:31,875 --> 00:19:33,416
where we cannot be together.

366
00:19:37,625 --> 00:19:39,208
That's true.

367
00:19:39,291 --> 00:19:41,166
We can't be together
in the way we want,

368
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:43,250
but I will always be with you.

369
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:45,250
In a world where not just
the strong survive,

370
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:47,291
and no one has
to step on each other.

371
00:19:47,375 --> 00:19:50,166
You and I are going to create
that reality together.

372
00:19:50,250 --> 00:19:51,875
If we do that, we'll never die.

373
00:19:52,875 --> 00:19:56,541
I will be there in every smile
and every laugh.

374
00:19:56,625 --> 00:19:59,666
I am never going to desert you,
Montmorency.

375
00:20:02,125 --> 00:20:03,958
[MONTMORENCY]
You're so foolish.

376
00:20:04,041 --> 00:20:06,958
You're starting to sound
like an actual saint.

377
00:20:07,041 --> 00:20:08,583
[MONTMORENCY sobbing quietly]

378
00:20:11,291 --> 00:20:15,166
I left you all alone,
and I was gone for far too long.

379
00:20:16,166 --> 00:20:17,708
But from now on,

380
00:20:17,791 --> 00:20:19,625
I'll stay by your side.

381
00:20:19,708 --> 00:20:21,083
Let's go.

382
00:20:21,166 --> 00:20:22,916
Come back to our world with me.

383
00:20:24,041 --> 00:20:27,375
[MONTMORENCY]
Yes, it is our world, isn't it?

384
00:20:34,208 --> 00:20:36,375
[ENLIL groaning]

385
00:20:36,458 --> 00:20:39,125
[screaming]

386
00:20:39,208 --> 00:20:41,750
[MONTMORENCY]
Get out of my body!

387
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:44,125
I banish you forever!

388
00:20:44,208 --> 00:20:46,666
♪

389
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,666
[gasps]

390
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:52,583
[ENLIL]
No, impossible.

391
00:20:52,666 --> 00:20:54,875
This simply can't be happening.

392
00:20:56,458 --> 00:20:57,541
[chuckles]

393
00:20:59,208 --> 00:21:02,000
[ENLIL]
Damn you, filthy human!

394
00:21:02,083 --> 00:21:03,708
Vessel in the sky!

395
00:21:03,791 --> 00:21:05,708
[screaming]

396
00:21:05,791 --> 00:21:06,916
No.

397
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,208
This is nothing
but a false utopia.

398
00:21:09,291 --> 00:21:11,291
You are wrong, fools.

399
00:21:11,375 --> 00:21:13,541
It must not be allowed to exist!

400
00:21:15,083 --> 00:21:17,500
♪

401
00:21:20,958 --> 00:21:22,833
We two have been chosen,

402
00:21:22,916 --> 00:21:26,250
but not by the gods,
and not by destiny.

403
00:21:26,333 --> 00:21:28,875
Yes, you chose me,
and I chose you.

404
00:21:29,875 --> 00:21:31,500
[MONTMORENCY]
Creating utopia.

405
00:21:31,583 --> 00:21:34,166
That must be something
that can't be achieved alone.

406
00:21:34,250 --> 00:21:35,833
We have to do it together.

407
00:21:35,916 --> 00:21:38,250
Our eternity will soon exist,

408
00:21:38,333 --> 00:21:40,750
but only in the world
that you and I will create.

409
00:21:40,833 --> 00:21:42,708
♪

410
00:21:44,416 --> 00:21:46,458
[ENLIL]
No. Impossible!

411
00:21:48,583 --> 00:21:50,875
Your time is over now, demon.

412
00:21:50,958 --> 00:21:52,375
We'll build our world,

413
00:21:52,458 --> 00:21:53,916
and with our own hands.

414
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,958
♪

415
00:23:28,166 --> 00:23:30,000
[NARRATOR] As we walk
through this world without gods,

416
00:23:30,083 --> 00:23:32,166
our footprints
will eventually disappear,

417
00:23:32,250 --> 00:23:33,958
yet our feelings
will endure forever.

418
00:23:34,041 --> 00:23:35,250
They shall be written
into history

419
00:23:35,333 --> 00:23:37,083
and passed down
till the end of time!

420
00:23:37,166 --> 00:23:38,125
Final episode.

421
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:39,250
"In this Wonderful World."

422
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:41,125
Viva la boobs!

423
00:23:44,125 --> 00:23:45,458
[MAN]
Proteges tes bijoux de famille.

